WHO   — The Prison Reckoning — Lamont, and the betrayal
WHAT  — The unlearning, earned through suffering and contact: the cause exposed as a lie, the enemy revealed as a friend.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film won't let reform be a switch — it's slow, painful, and partly forced by the movement's own cruelty.
HOW   — By pairing Derek with Lamont until the hate had no object, and letting the Brotherhood's betrayal finish the job.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am where it broke: a friend the hate couldn't survive, and a betrayal by the men the hate was for.

